CHANGES0141 — Make isOpenProp a proposition (Σ → ∥ Σ ∥₁)

Changes since bck0141 pre-state (6064 lines → 6093 lines, +29 lines):

The line increase is expected and necessary: wrapping bare pattern matches
in PT.rec/PT.rec2/PT.map requires adding type-annotated `go` helper functions.

Motivation: isOpenProp was a bare Σ-type, not a proposition. The user requested
it be made propositional (∥ Σ ∥₁), matching the earlier isClosedProp change
(bck0133). No postulates introduced.

Design: Two-level API
  - isOpenWitness P = Σ[ α ∈ binarySequence ] ⟨ P ⟩ ↔ (Σ[ n ∈ ℕ ] α n ≡ true)
  - isOpenProp P = ∥ isOpenWitness P ∥₁
  - isPropIsOpenProp = squash₁
  Producers wrap in ∣ ... ∣₁. Consumers use PT.rec/PT.rec2 to extract.

